{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase the income threshold for people repaying student loans under Plan 1",
        "additional_details": "I feel students who started an undergraduate course before 1 September 2012 are being treated unfairly.\r\n \r\nStudents on Plan 1 did not choose when to graduate from further education and start university, but have to start repaying their loan if they earn more than \u00a31615 before tax.\r\n\r\nAny students on Plan 2, who started after 1 September 2012, only need to start repaying when they earn above \u00a32214 before tax.\r\n \r\nThese earning limits should be equal.",
        "background": "All students should have the same income threshold irrespective of when they started university. Students on Plan 1 should start repaying at same earning limits as students on Plan 2.",
